
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `evince` baraye baz kardan va didan file-haye PDF, PostScript, va format-haye digar estefade mishavad. In yek barnam-ye namayesh-dehandeye asnade grafiki ast ke besiar rahat va sade ast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `evince filename.pdf`  --> 📄 Baz kardane yek file PDF khass.
    🔹 `evince`  --> 💻 Baz kardane barnam-ye evince be soorate mostaghel (bedune file khass).
    🔹 `evince -w`  --> 👓 Baz kardan dar panjere-ye jadid.
    🔹 `evince --presentation` --> 🎬 Baz kardan file be soorate namayesh (presentation mode).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ evince ketab.pdf

    🔹 Baz kardane file PDF "ketab.pdf" ba estefade az barnam-ye evince.

    $ evince report.ps

    🔹 Baz kardane file PostScript "report.ps".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ evince maghale.pdf &

    🔹 Baz kardane file "maghale.pdf" dar pas-zamine (background) ta shoma betavanid karhaye digar ra anjam dahid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `evince` command is used to open and view PDF files, PostScript files, and other document formats. It's a user-friendly document viewer known for its simplicity.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `evince filename.pdf`  --> 📄 Open a specific PDF file.
    🔹 `evince`  --> 💻 Launch the Evince application independently (without a specific file).
    🔹 `evince -w`  --> 👓 Open in a new window.
    🔹 `evince --presentation` --> 🎬 Open the file in presentation mode.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ evince book.pdf

    🔹 Open the PDF file "book.pdf" using the Evince application.

    $ evince report.ps

    🔹 Open the PostScript file "report.ps".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ evince article.pdf &

    🔹 Open the file "article.pdf" in the background so you can continue with other tasks.
